      <description>Fred Matthews was born in West Feliciana Parish, La., on February 1,
            1906. Matthews worked at the Standard Oil (Esso) Refinery, now Exxon/Mobil, for nearly
            forty years. He was the highest ranking and highest paid African American there for many
            years. Matthews was married and had three children. He worked in publicity for Baptist
            churches for twenty-five years and was a World War II veteran. Matthews passed away in
            2002 at age 95.</description>
