   <abstract xlink:href="http://lib.lsu.edu/services/oralhistory/abstracts/mckinley/2_businesses/Legard_Eva_T1033.pdf">Matthews discusses the movement of farmers to Baton Rouge in the 1920s, and African
            American businesses in the South Baton Rouge community. Matthews mainly recalls his
            career at Standard Oil and advancements in oil refining techniques. He describes race
            relations at Exxon over the years, and the upward mobility of African Americans within
            the company after the Civil Rights Act. He speculates on the rise and fall of African
            American-owned businesses in Baton Rouge.</abstract>
